node.text:
I totally understand that the United States of America and CDC felt the need to do certain things to "protect"  the American people but what I don't appreciate is the fact that it seems that they hand-picked what they choose to do for the people. If you are going to do a moratorium where it's affecting people financial in terms of paying their rents or their mortgages you should also have had a moratorium or a forgiveness to the taxes and other government  fees that the people of this country has to pay daily , for example Tolls , utilities, etc .I find it odd that whatever is owed to the country in terms of taxes and other fees the government not once forgave, stopped, or put a moratorium in place for that, because the givern6eabts to make sure they get their money right ? So I blame the United States of America first for what's going on. Your suppose to take care of the people !!

I totally understand that the United States of America and CDC felt the need to do certain things to "protect"  the American people but what I don't appreciate is the fact that it seems that they hand-picked what they choose to do for the people. If you are going to do a moratorium where it's affecting people financial in terms of paying their rents or their mortgages you should also have had a moratorium or a forgiveness to the taxes and other government  fees that the people of this country has to pay daily , for example Tolls , utilities, etc .I find it odd that whatever is owed to the country in terms of taxes and other fees the government not once forgave, stopped, or put a moratorium in place for that, because the givern6eabts to make sure they get their money right ? So I blame the United States of America first for what's going on. Your suppose to take care of the people !!
